index.pages.register.desc.message: To use the WhaTap monitoring service, proceed with membership registration. Try free for 15 days.

index.pages.project.desc.message: Create a project, and then issue an access key.

index.pages.agentInstall.desc.message: Install agent to the monitoring target.

index.pages.viewDashboard.desc.message: When data is transferred to the WhaTap server after agent installation, you can view the overall project status in real time through dashboard.

index.pages.welcome.para.message: Welcome to the WhaTap Docs page.

index.pages.section.gettingStart.support.message: You can check the support environment before using our service.

index.pages.section.gettingStart.home.de.message: It guides you to the elements displayed on the initial screen

index.pages.section.gettingStart.mobileA.message: It guides you to the functions available through the WhaTap mobile app.

index.pages.section.product.java.message: Applies to all applications running on the JVM environment, such as WAS and batch applications etc.

index.pages.section.product.nodejs.message: Single thread flows can be analyzed every 10 seconds to identfy bottlenecks or errors by using asynchronous transaction anaysis.

index.pages.section.product.php.message: Supports upto PHP 8.3 and Alpine Linux. SQL, HTTP call, Redis call information can be checked on the profile.

index.pages.section.product.python.message: Applies to major applications such as web framework, server, and batch. Delays can be identified by tracing DB queries and external calls.

index.pages.section.product.dotnet.message: Monitors .NET based IIS, Console, Service, Windows applications in the .NET Frameworks 4.5 environment.

index.pages.section.product.go.message: Go API can be used to trace web requests, response transactions, unit transactions, SQL, HTTP calls, and more of Go application.

index.pages.section.product.server.message: Supports physical servers, cloud, scale-out environments. Also, large-scale resources and risky resources with high utilization rates can be monitored and managed.

index.pages.section.product.k8s.message: Monitors Kubernetes clusters, nodes, applications, and logs at a glance.

index.pages.section.product.postgresql.message: Monitors, analyzes and compares performance indicators, SQL, Lock, and Slow SQL.

index.pages.section.product.oracle.message: Monitors, analyzes and compares performance indicators, SQL, Lock, and parallel query information.

index.pages.section.product.oraclePro.message: By directly accessing the memory of the database server, performance information can be monitored dozens of times per second without loading the database server.

index.pages.section.product.mysql.message: Monitors, analyzes and compares MySQL and MariaDB’s performance indicators, SQL, Lock, Slow SQL.

index.pages.section.product.mssql.message: Monitors, analyzes and compares performance indicators, SQL and Lock information.

index.pages.section.product.tibero.message: Monitors, analyzes and compares performance indicators, SQL, Lock, and parallel query information.

index.pages.section.product.cubrid.message: Monitors, analyzes and compares performance indicators, SQL, Lock, and parallel query information.

index.pages.section.product.altibase.message: Monitors, analyzes and compares performance indicators, SQL, Lock, and parallel query information.

index.pages.section.product.redis.message: Monitors, analyzes and compares performance indicators.

index.pages.section.product.mongodb.message: Monitors, analyzes and compares performance indicators.

index.pages.section.product.url.message: Connectivity issues can be automatically checked with HTTP status codes as an end user.

index.pages.section.product.browser.message: Monitors and analyzes the performance of end-user interactions with browser applications.

index.pages.section.product.awsCloudWatc.message: Retrieves and stores metrics periodically through the Amazon CloudWatch API.

index.pages.section.product.awsEcs.message: Collects resource usage by Docker container in real time through META API and cgroup directory.

index.pages.section.product.awsLog.message: Collects and saves logs that are created in AWS Resources and stored in AWS S3 and AWS CloudWatch Log Group.

index.pages.section.product.azure.message: Searches and saves metrics periodically through the Azure Monitor API.

index.pages.section.product.ncloud.message: Searches and saves metrics periodically through the Naver Cloud Monitoring API.

index.pages.section.product.oci.message: Searches and saves metrics periodically through the Oracle Cloud Monitor API.

index.pages.section.product.network.message: It visualizes the network communication information of the process and uses it to analyze performance and identify failures.

index.pages.section.product.feature.message: It provides an optimized monitoring solution by repackaging existing monitoring products to fit the software to monitor.

index.pages.section.management.account.d.message: Signup up to create and manage your account.

index.pages.section.management.multiFact.message: Multi-factor authentication can be used to enhance the security of accounts and services.

index.pages.section.management.sso.desc.message: Log in easily using a single ID and password.

index.pages.section.management.billing.d.message: Get started with a trial version for free and use as much as you need.

index.pages.section.management.project.d.message: The project means a monitoring unit. Learn more about the project.

index.pages.section.management.organize..message: You can systematically manage organizations, groups, and projects.

index.pages.section.management.maintenan.message: You can pause notification set to receive during the registered maintenance time.

index.pages.section.management.userbehav.message: You can track user actions being performed in the project.

index.pages.section.updates.news.desc.message: Check out the newly released features.

index.pages.section.updates.release.desc.message: Quickly check the latest release information.

index.pages.section.reference.openApi.de.message: You can extract monitoring data through the Open API.

index.pages.section.reference.proxy.desc.message: You can block access to the external network and send data to the WhaTap server through a single channel.

index.pages.section.reference.docs.desc.message: WhaTap Docs can help you efficiently use WhaTap Monitoring.

index.pages.section.reference.license.de.message: Guides the open source licenses and available libraries used by WhaTap.

index.pages.section.reference.faq.desc.message: It provides solutions to common problems that may occur while using the WhaTap monitoring service.

index.pages.section.learn.learning.desc.message: We provide learning materials for quick understanding and efficient use of the WhaTap.

index.pages.section.learn.mxql.desc.message: MXQL is a query language to flexibly query WhaTap's performance data (metrics).

index.pages.section.learn.metrics.desc.message: Metrics is the data collected from the monitoring target.

index.pages.section.learn.glossary.desc.message: A glossary of terms is provided for easier use of the monitoring service.
